<br>
I was going to pick the Wizard class anyway, but I saw one bit of information that clinched it for me instantly.  Wizards were to be the Planar travelers, able to open gates to and from the Planes.  Naturally, there was no way to know that the Planes that would eventually be released (Fear and Hate) would be so deadly to the solo adventurer.  But the idea was there, and I was instantly drawn to the Wizard.  Hence I played a Wiz in Beta and created Abadacus immediately upon EQ's commercial release.<br>
<br>
Over time, it became apparent that Wizards were somewhat at a disadvantage, having only their mana to defend themselves by, as compared to the other Robed classes that had pets.  Mana was a harsh limiting factor on Wizards for a very long time, and the numbers of Wizards declined as the game progressed.  Even so, I thoroughly enjoyed my class, and never had any reservations about my choice of class.<br>
<br>
Fast forward to today.  Never in the history of Wizards have we been as well off as we are today.  Mana is no longer a problem, and the sheer pleasure of playing my class is as fresh and vibrant as it was when I first started, but with far less limitations.  As has been posted in this thread, I too enjoy the high crits, the ability to travel at will, and the pleasure of quading, not to mention raiding the high end game which is in and of itself a great deal of fun.<br>
<br>
I've started out many twinks, but none have been as fun to me as my Wizard.<br>
<br>
